Description: IB fabric build-deps: add cuda-nvml-dev, drop libpmix-dev.
 cuda-nvml-dev-13-2 ships nvml.h at /usr/local/cuda/include/nvml.h and a
 link-time libnvidia-ml.so stub under /usr/local/cuda/lib64/stubs, which
 is what Slurm's --with-nvml=/usr/local/cuda configure flag consumes to
 enable the mpi/gpu_nvml autodetect plugin at build time (runtime
 libnvidia-ml.so.1 is injected by nvidia-container-toolkit from the host
 driver).
 libpmix-dev is dropped because the IB image runs DOCA's OpenMPI 4 which
 ships its own internal PMIx tangled with libopen-pal/libevent/hwloc.
 Per NVIDIA HPC-X docs, slurm's PMIx server plugin requires Open MPI to
 be built against the SAME external PMIx — DOCA's OMPI is not. The IB
 path therefore launches under slurm via PMI2 (mpi_pmi2.so + libpmi2)
 and slurm is built without PMIx server support entirely.
Author: meshy-dev
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-06
